com.stripe.android.model

Class KlarnaSourceParams

  • com.stripe.android.model.KlarnaSourceParams
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StripeParamsModel

    public class KlarnaSourceParams
implements StripeParamsModel

    Model representing parameters for creating a Klarna Source.

    See Klarna Payments with Sources

    Note: The optional fields billingEmail, billingPhone, billingAddress, billingFirstName, billingLastName, and billingDob can be provided to skip Klarna's customer information form.

    If this information is missing, Klarna will prompt the customer for these values during checkout. Be careful with this option: If the provided information is invalid, Klarna may reject the transaction without giving the customer a chance to correct it.

    See Also:

        public KlarnaSourceParams(java.lang.String purchaseCountry,
                          java.util.List<com.stripe.android.model.KlarnaSourceParams.LineItem> lineItems,
                          java.util.Set<? extends com.stripe.android.model.KlarnaSourceParams.CustomPaymentMethods> customPaymentMethods,
                          java.lang.String billingEmail,
                          java.lang.String billingPhone,
                          Address billingAddress,
                          java.lang.String billingFirstName,

                          DateOfBirth billingDob,
                          KlarnaSourceParams.PaymentPageOptions pageOptions)

        Model representing parameters for creating a Klarna Source.

        See Klarna Payments with Sources

        Note: The optional fields billingEmail, billingPhone, billingAddress, billingFirstName, billingLastName, and billingDob can be provided to skip Klarna's customer information form.

        If this information is missing, Klarna will prompt the customer for these values during checkout. Be careful with this option: If the provided information is invalid, Klarna may reject the transaction without giving the customer a chance to correct it.

        Parameters:
        purchaseCountry - The URL the customer should be redirected to after they have successfully verified thepayment.
        lineItems - A list of class KlarnaSourceParams.LineItem. Klarna will present these on the confirmation page.The total amount charged will be a sum of the LineItem.totalAmount of each of these items.
        customPaymentMethods - Required for customers located in the US. This determines whether Pay Later and/or Slice Itis offered to a US customer.
        billingEmail -

        An email address for the customer.

        Optional

        billingPhone -

        A phone number for the customer.

        Optional

        billingAddress -

        An class Address for the customer. At a minimum, Address.line1, Address.postalCode, Address.city, and Address.country must be provided.

        Optional

        billingFirstName -

        The customer's first name.

        Optional

        billingLastName -

        The customer's last name.

        Optional

        billingDob -

        The customer's date of birth. This will be used by Klarna for a credit check in some EU countries.

        Optional

        pageOptions -

        See Styling the Klarna Hosted Payment Page

        You can customize the style of the Klarna hosted payment page by providing additional options when creating the source. Refer to the Klarna SDK documentation for more information.

        See Also:
